370    public void initialize() throws Exception
371    {
372        try
373        {
374            initializeSessionManagerInterfaces();
375 
376            eventChannel = EventChannelAdapterFactory.find();
377            eventChannel.setDynamicChannels(true);
378            eventChannel.setListenerCleanup(CommonTranslatorProperties.isCleanChannelAdapterEnabled());
379 
380            initializeCallbackConsumers();
381 
382            initializeCaches();
383 
384            systemAdminProductProcessor = new SystemAdminProductProcessor();
385            systemAdminProductProcessor.subscribeForProductEvents();
386 
387            ProductConfigurationQueryAPIFactory.create(systemAdminSessionManager.getProductConfigurationService());
388        }
389        catch (Exception e)
390        {
391            GUILoggerHome.find().exception(TRANSLATOR_NAME + ": SystemAdminAPIImpl.initialize", e);
392            throw e;
393        }

509    /**
510     * Initializes the exchange:product_set cache
511     */
512    public synchronized void initializeExchangeToUnderlyingProductsCache()
513    {
514        if(!exchangeToUnderlyingCacheInitialized)
515        {
516            boolean logInformation = false;
517            try
518            {
519                exchangeProductMappingCache = ExchangeProductMappingCache.getInstance();
520                if(GUILoggerHome.find().isInformationOn() &&
521                   GUILoggerHome.find().isPropertyOn(GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.PRODUCT_QUERY))
522                {
523                    logInformation = true;
524                    GUILoggerHome.find().information(TRANSLATOR_NAME +
525                                                     ":initializeExchangeToUnderlyingProductsCache() - starting to load Exchange->UnderlyingProducts cache",
526                                                     GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.PRODUCT_QUERY);
527                }
528                exchangeProductMappingCache.initializeCache();
529                exchangeProductMappingCache.subscribeForEvents();
530                exchangeToUnderlyingCacheInitialized = true;
531            }
532            catch(UserException e)
533            {
534                GUILoggerHome.find().exception(
535                        TRANSLATOR_NAME + ": .initializeExchangeProductMappingCache()", "", e);
536            }
537            if(logInformation)
538            {
539                GUILoggerHome.find().information(TRANSLATOR_NAME +
540                                                 ":initializeExchangeToUnderlyingProductsCache() - finished to load Exchange->UnderlyingProducts cache",
541                                                 GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.PRODUCT_QUERY);
542            }
543        }
544    }
545 
546    /**
547     * Cleanup of exchange to product cache.
548     */
549    protected void cleanupExchangeToUnderlyingProductsCache()
550    {
551        exchangeProductMappingCache.unsubscribeForEvents();
552        exchangeProductMappingCache.clear();
553        exchangeProductMappingCache = null;
554    }
555 
556    public synchronized void initializeUnderlyingProductToSessionClassesCache()
557            throws SystemException, CommunicationException, AuthorizationException, DataValidationException
558    {
559        if(!underlyingToClassCacheInitialized)
560        {
561            boolean logInformation = false;
562            if(GUILoggerHome.find().isInformationOn() &&
563               GUILoggerHome.find().isPropertyOn(GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.PRODUCT_QUERY))
564            {
565                logInformation = true;
566                GUILoggerHome.find().information(TRANSLATOR_NAME +
567                                                 ":initializeUnderlyingProductToSessionClassesCache() - starting to load UnderlyingProduct->SessionProductClasses cache",
568                                                 GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.PRODUCT_QUERY);
569            }
570            //load underlyingProduct->SessionProductClasses cache for each session
571            com.cboe.idl.cmiSession.TradingSessionStruct[] tradingSessions = getCurrentTradingSessions(null);
572            for(com.cboe.idl.cmiSession.TradingSessionStruct tradingSession : tradingSessions)
573            {
574                try
575                {
576                    ProductType[] productTypes = getProductTypesForSession(tradingSession.sessionName);
577                    for(int i = 0; i < productTypes.length; i++)
578                    {
579                        loadUnderlyingProductToSessionClassesCache(tradingSession.sessionName, productTypes[i].getType());
580                    }
581                    underlyingToClassCacheInitialized = true;
582                }
583                catch(Exception e)
584                {
585                    GUILoggerHome.find().exception(TRANSLATOR_NAME + ": .initializeUnderlyingProductToSessionClassCache()", "", e);
586                }
587            }
588            if(logInformation)
589            {
590                GUILoggerHome.find().information(TRANSLATOR_NAME +
591                                                 ":initializeUnderlyingProductToSessionClassesCache() - finished loading UnderlyingProduct->SessionProductClasses cache",
592                                                 GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.PRODUCT_QUERY);
593            }
594        }
595    }
596 
597    /**
598     * Loads the product:sessionClassSet cache.
599     */
600    private void loadUnderlyingProductToSessionClassesCache(String sessionName, short productType) throws
601            DataValidationException, AuthorizationException, CommunicationException, SystemException
602    {
603        SessionProductClass[] productClasses = getAllProductClassesForSession(sessionName);
604        if(productClasses != null && productClasses.length > 0)
605        {
606            if(GUILoggerHome.find().isInformationOn() &&
607               GUILoggerHome.find().isPropertyOn(GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.PRODUCT_QUERY))
608            {
609                GUILoggerHome.find()
610                        .information(TRANSLATOR_NAME +
611                                     ":loadUnderlyingProductToSessionClassesCache() - processing " +
612                                     productClasses.length +
613                                     " SessionProductClasses for session='" + sessionName +
614                                     "' productType='" + ProductTypes.toString(productType) +
615                                     "'", GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.PRODUCT_QUERY);
616            }
617            productProcessor.populateProductKeyToSessionClassesCache(sessionName, productClasses);
618        }
619        else
620        {
621            if(GUILoggerHome.find().isInformationOn() &&
622               GUILoggerHome.find().isPropertyOn(GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.PRODUCT_QUERY))
623            {
624                GUILoggerHome.find()
625                        .information(TRANSLATOR_NAME +
626                                     ":loadUnderlyingProductToSessionClassesCache() - no SessionProductClasses to process for session='" +
627                                     sessionName + "' productType='" +
628                                     ProductTypes.toString(productType) + "'",
629                                     GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.PRODUCT_QUERY);
630            }
631        }
632    }
633 
634    public RegisteredServer[] getTradingSessionRegistrationNames()
635            throws DataValidationException, AuthorizationException, TransactionFailedException, CommunicationException,
636            SystemException
637    {
638        if (GUILoggerHome.find().isDebugOn() &&
639                GUILoggerHome.find().isPropertyOn(GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.SESSION_MANAGEMENT))
640        {
641            GUILoggerHome.find().debug(TRANSLATOR_NAME + ":getTradingSessionRegistrationNames",
642                                       GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.SESSION_MANAGEMENT);
643        }
644 
645        TradingSessionRegistrationStruct[] structs = tradingSessionService.getTradingSessionRegistrationNames();
646 
647        if (GUILoggerHome.find().isDebugOn() &&
648                GUILoggerHome.find().isPropertyOn(GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.SESSION_MANAGEMENT))
649        {
650            GUILoggerHome.find().debug(TRANSLATOR_NAME + ":getTradingSessionRegistrationNames",
651                                       GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.SESSION_MANAGEMENT, structs);
652        }
653 
654        ArrayList<RegisteredServer> list = new ArrayList<RegisteredServer>(structs.length * 5);
655        for (int i = 0; i < structs.length; i++)
656        {
657            TradingSessionRegistrationStruct tradingSessionRegistrationStruct = structs[i];
658            RegisteredServer[] servers = RegisteredServerFactory.createRegisteredServers(tradingSessionRegistrationStruct);
659            for (int j = 0; j < servers.length; j++)
660            {
661                RegisteredServer server = servers[j];
662                list.add(server);
663            }
664        }
665        RegisteredServer[] servers = new RegisteredServer[list.size()];
666        if (list.size() > 0)
667        {
668            servers = list.toArray(servers);
669        }
670 
671        return servers;
672    }
673 
674    public RegisteredServerEvent[] getRegisteredServersEventState(String sessionName)
675            throws DataValidationException, AuthorizationException, TransactionFailedException, CommunicationException,
676            SystemException
677    {
678        if (GUILoggerHome.find().isDebugOn() &&
679                GUILoggerHome.find().isPropertyOn(GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.SESSION_MANAGEMENT))
680        {
681            GUILoggerHome.find().debug(TRANSLATOR_NAME + ":getRegisteredServersEventState",
682                                       GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.SESSION_MANAGEMENT, sessionName);
683        }
684 
685        TradingSessionServerEventStateStruct[] eventStructs =
686                tradingSessionService.getRegisteredServersEventState(sessionName);
687 
688        if (GUILoggerHome.find().isDebugOn() &&
689                GUILoggerHome.find().isPropertyOn(GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.SESSION_MANAGEMENT))
690        {
691            GUILoggerHome.find().debug(TRANSLATOR_NAME + ":getRegisteredServersEventState",
692                                       GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.SESSION_MANAGEMENT, eventStructs);
693        }
694 
695        RegisteredServerEvent[] events = new RegisteredServerEvent[eventStructs.length];
696        for (int i = 0; i < eventStructs.length; i++)
697        {
698            TradingSessionServerEventStateStruct eventStruct = eventStructs[i];
699            events[i] = RegisteredServerEventFactory.createRegisteredServer(eventStruct);
700        }
701 
702        return events;
703    }

705    public TradingSessionEvent[] getEventHistoryV2(String sessionName)
706            throws DataValidationException, AuthorizationException, TransactionFailedException, CommunicationException,
707            SystemException
708    {
709        if (GUILoggerHome.find().isDebugOn() &&
710                GUILoggerHome.find().isPropertyOn(GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.SESSION_MANAGEMENT))
711        {
712            GUILoggerHome.find().debug(TRANSLATOR_NAME + ":getEventHistoryV2",
713                                       GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.SESSION_MANAGEMENT, sessionName);
714        }
715 
716        TradingSessionEventHistoryStructV2[] eventHistoryStructs = tradingSessionService.getEventHistoryV2(sessionName);
717 
718        if (GUILoggerHome.find().isDebugOn() &&
719                GUILoggerHome.find().isPropertyOn(GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.SESSION_MANAGEMENT))
720        {
721            GUILoggerHome.find().debug(TRANSLATOR_NAME + ":getEventHistoryV2",
722                                       GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.SESSION_MANAGEMENT, eventHistoryStructs);
723        }
724 
725        TradingSessionEvent[] events = new TradingSessionEvent[eventHistoryStructs.length];
726        for (int i = 0; i < eventHistoryStructs.length; i++)
727        {
728            TradingSessionEventHistoryStructV2 eventHistoryStructV2 = eventHistoryStructs[i];
729            events[i] = TradingSessionEventFactory.createTradingSessionEvent(eventHistoryStructV2);
730        }
731 
732        return events;
733    }

2443    private void disconnectConsumers(org.omg.CORBA.Object[] consumers)
2444    {

2446        {
2447            disconnectConsumer(consumers[i]);
2448        }
2449    }

2451    private void disconnectConsumer(org.omg.CORBA.Object consumer)
2452    {
2453        try
2454        {
2455            POAHelper.disconnect(POAHelper.reference_to_servant(consumer, null), null);
2456        }
2457        catch (Exception e)
2458        {
2459            GUILoggerHome.find().exception(Category + ".disconnectConsumer", "Error disconnecting user consumer::" + consumer, e);
2460        }
2461    }

3070 
3071    public void subscribeProductStatusByKey(int classKey, EventChannelListener clientListener)
3072            throws SystemException, CommunicationException, DataValidationException, AuthorizationException
3073    {
3074        if (GUILoggerHome.find().isDebugOn())
3075        {
3076            Object[] argObj = new Object[2];
3077            argObj[0] = new Integer(classKey);
3078            argObj[1] = clientListener;
3079            GUILoggerHome.find().debug(TRANSLATOR_NAME + ":subscribeProductStatusByKey", GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.PRODUCT_MAINTENANCE, argObj);
3080        }
3081        ChannelKey key = new ChannelKey(ChannelType.PQS_UPDATE_PRODUCT, new Integer(classKey));
3082        int subscriptionCount1 = SubscriptionManagerFactory.find().subscribe(key, clientListener, adminProductStatusConsumer);
3083        key = new ChannelKey(ChannelType.PQS_STRATEGY_UPDATE, new Integer(classKey));
3084        int subscriptionCount2 = SubscriptionManagerFactory.find().subscribe(key, clientListener, adminProductStatusConsumer);
3085        if (subscriptionCount1 == 1 && subscriptionCount2 == 1)
3086        {
3087             productMaintenance.subscribeProductStatusByKey(classKey, adminProductStatusConsumer);
3088        }
3089    }
3090 
3091    public void subscribeClassStatus(short productType, EventChannelListener clientListener)
3092        throws SystemException, CommunicationException, DataValidationException, AuthorizationException
3093    {
3094        if (GUILoggerHome.find().isDebugOn())
3095        {
3096            GUILoggerHome.find().debug(TRANSLATOR_NAME + ":subscribeClassStatus", GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.PRODUCT_MAINTENANCE, clientListener);
3097        }
3098        ChannelKey key = new ChannelKey(ChannelType.PQS_UPDATE_PRODUCT_CLASS, new Integer(productType));
3099        if (SubscriptionManagerFactory.find().subscribe(key, clientListener, adminProductStatusConsumer) == 1)

6841    public PropertyGroupStruct setProperties(PropertyGroupStruct properties)
6842            throws SystemException, CommunicationException, AuthorizationException
6843    {
6844        if (GUILoggerHome.find().isDebugOn() &&
6845           GUILoggerHome.find().isPropertyOn(GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.PROPERTY_SERVICE))
6846        {
6847            GUILoggerHome.find().debug(TRANSLATOR_NAME + ":setProperties INPUT",
6848                                       GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.PROPERTY_SERVICE, properties);
6849        }
6850 
6851        boolean doSAGUICentralLogging = false;
6852        if(null != properties && null != properties.category && PropertyCategoryTypes.TRADING_PROPERTIES.equals(properties.category))
6853        {
6854            doSAGUICentralLogging = true;
6855        }
6856 
6857        String oldProperties = null;
6858        if(doSAGUICentralLogging)
6859        {
6860            try
6861            {
6862                PropertyGroupStruct oldPropertiesStruct =
6863                        getProperties(properties.category, properties.propertyKey);
6864                oldProperties = TradingPropertyCentralLogger
6865                        .getFormattedTradingProperties(oldPropertiesStruct);
6866            }
6867            catch(NotFoundException nfe)
6868            {
6869                GUILoggerHome.find().debug(TRANSLATOR_NAME + ":setProperties INPUT",
6870                                           GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.PROPERTY_SERVICE,
6871                                           "getProperties() for SAGUICentralLogging failed :" +
6872                                           nfe);
6873                oldProperties = TradingPropertyCentralLogger.NONE;
6874            }
6875        }
6876 
6877        PropertyGroupStruct returnStructs = propertyService.setProperties(properties);
6878 
6879        if (GUILoggerHome.find().isAuditOn())
6880        {
6881            GUILoggerHome.find().audit(formatLogProperty(GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.PROPERTY_SERVICE),
6882                                       "setProperties", properties);
6883            if(doSAGUICentralLogging)
6884            {
6885                String messageText = TradingPropertyCentralLogger.getMessageText(
6886                        TradingPropertyCentralLogger.OPERATION_ADD_UPDATE, oldProperties,
6887                        returnStructs);
6888                GUILoggerHome.find().nonRepudiationAudit(
6889                        TradingPropertyCentralLogger.TRADING_PROPERTY_AUDIT, messageText);
6890            }
6891        }
6892        if (GUILoggerHome.find().isDebugOn() &&
6893           GUILoggerHome.find().isPropertyOn(GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.PROPERTY_SERVICE))
6894        {
6895            GUILoggerHome.find().debug(TRANSLATOR_NAME + ":setProperties OUTPUT",
6896                                       GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.PROPERTY_SERVICE, returnStructs);
6897        }
6898 
6899        return returnStructs;
6900    }

6969        if(category != null && PropertyCategoryTypes.TRADING_PROPERTIES.equals(category))
6970        {
6971            doSAGUICentralLogging = true;
6972        }
6973 
6974        String messageText = null;
6975        if(doSAGUICentralLogging)
6976        {
6977            try
6978            {
6979                PropertyGroupStruct struct = getProperties(category, propertyKey);
6980                messageText =
6981                        TradingPropertyCentralLogger.getMessageTextForRemoveProperties(struct);
6982            }
6983            catch(NotFoundException nfe)
6984            {
6985                GUILoggerHome.find().debug(TRANSLATOR_NAME + ":removeProperties",
6986                                           GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.PROPERTY_SERVICE,
6987                                           "getProperties() for SAGUICentralLogging failed :" + nfe);
6988                messageText = TradingPropertyCentralLogger.NONE;
6989            }
6990        }
6991 
6992        propertyService.removeProperties(category, propertyKey);
6993 
6994        if (GUILoggerHome.find().isAuditOn())
6995        {
6996            GUILoggerHome.find().audit(formatLogProperty(GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.PROPERTY_SERVICE),
6997                                       "removeProperties", argObj);
6998            if(doSAGUICentralLogging)
6999            {
7000                GUILoggerHome.find().nonRepudiationAudit(
7001                        TradingPropertyCentralLogger.TRADING_PROPERTY_AUDIT, messageText);
7002            }
7003        }
7004    }

8535     /**
8536     * getOrdersForProduct
8537     * <p/>
8538     * This method calls the existing OHS method, getOrdersForProduct, translating the
8539     * UserDefinitionStruct to the userId ( string ) and repackaging the return OrderStruct[]
8540     * to an OrderDetailStruct[]
8541     */
8542    public OrderDetailStruct[] getOrderDetailsForProduct(String userId, int productKey)
8543        throws SystemException, CommunicationException, DataValidationException, AuthorizationException, NotFoundException
8544    {
8545        if (GUILoggerHome.find().isDebugOn())
8546        {
8547            Object[] argObj = new Object[2];
8548            argObj[0] = userId;
8549            argObj[1] = new Integer(productKey);
8550 
8551            GUILoggerHome.find().debug(TRANSLATOR_NAME + ":getOrdersForProduct",
8552                                       GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.ORDER_HANDLING, argObj);
8553        }
8554 
8555        OrderStruct[]           orderStructSequence         = null;
8556        OrderDetailStruct[]     orderDetailStructSequence   = null;
8557        OrderDetailStruct       orderDetailStruct           = null;
8558        int                     i;
8559        int                     orderLength;
8560 
8561        orderStructSequence = getOrdersForProduct(userId, productKey);
8562 
8563        if (orderStructSequence != null)
8564        {
8565            if (GUILoggerHome.find().isDebugOn())
8566            {
8567                GUILoggerHome.find().debug(TRANSLATOR_NAME + ":getOrdersForProduct.orderStructSequence",
8568                                           GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.ORDER_HANDLING, orderStructSequence);
8569            }
8570 
8571            orderLength = orderStructSequence.length;
8572            orderDetailStructSequence = new OrderDetailStruct[ orderLength ];
8573            for (i = 0; i < orderLength; i++)
8574            {
8575                orderDetailStruct = buildOrderDetailStruct(orderStructSequence[i]);
8576                if (orderDetailStruct == null)
8577                {
8578                    throw ExceptionBuilder.notFoundException("Unable to find product name information for productkey:" + productKey, 0);
8579                }
8580                orderDetailStructSequence[i] = orderDetailStruct;
8581            }
8582        }
8583 
8584        return orderDetailStructSequence;
8585    }
8586 
8587 
8588    /*
8589      * Helper method to build a CAS order detail struct from the CBOE order struct.
8590      * @param order OrderStruct  The CBOE Business order object.
8591      * @return OrderDetailStruct
8592      */
8593    private OrderDetailStruct buildOrderDetailStruct(OrderStruct order)
8594    {
8595        int[]               productKeys = {order.productKey};
8596        ProductNameStruct   productName     = null;
8597        try
8598        {
8599            productName = systemAdminSessionManager.getProductQuery().getProductNameStruct(order.productKey);
8600        }
8601        catch (Exception e)
8602        {
8603            GUILoggerHome.find().exception(Category + ".buildOrderDetailStruct", "Unable to retrieve productNameStruct for productKey:" + order.productKey, e);
8604            return null;
8605        }
8606        return new OrderDetailStruct(productName, StatusUpdateReasons.QUERY, order);
8607    }

9470    public void subscribeTradingSessionEventState(EventChannelListener clientListener)
9471           throws SystemException, CommunicationException, AuthorizationException, DataValidationException
9472    {
9473        ChannelKey key = new ChannelKey(ChannelType.TRADING_SESSION_EVENT_STATE, new Integer(0));
9474 
9475        if (GUILoggerHome.find().isDebugOn())
9476        {
9477            GUILoggerHome.find().debug(TRANSLATOR_NAME + ":subscribeTradingSessionEventState",
9478                                       GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.TRADING_SESSION, clientListener);
9479        }
9480 
9481        if (SubscriptionManagerFactory.find().subscribe(key, clientListener, tradingSessionEventStateConsumer) == 1)
9482        {
9483            tradingSessionEventStateService.subscribeTradingSessionEventState(tradingSessionEventStateConsumer);
9484        }
9485 
9486        key = new ChannelKey(ChannelType.CB_TRADING_SESSION_EVENT_STATE, new Integer(0));
9487        EventChannelAdapterFactory.find().addChannelListener(EventChannelAdapterFactory.find(), clientListener, key);
9488    }

9655        throws NotFoundException, SystemException, CommunicationException, AuthorizationException, DataValidationException
9656    {
9657        if (GUILoggerHome.find().isDebugOn())
9658        {
9659            GUILoggerHome.find().debug(TRANSLATOR_NAME + ":getProductByKey", GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.PRODUCT_QUERY, productKey);
9660        }
9661 
9662        Product product = null;
9663 
9664        if (productKey == DEFAULT_PRODUCT_KEY)
9665        {
9666            product = getDefaultProduct();
9667        }
9668        else if (productKey == ALL_SELECTED_PRODUCT_KEY)
9669        {
9670            product = getAllSelectedProduct();
9671        }
9672        else if (productKey == DEFAULT_STRATEGY_PRODUCT_KEY)
9673        {
9674            product = getDefaultStrategy();
9675        }
9676        else
9677        {
9678            int[] keys = {productKey};
9679            product = ProductFactoryHome.find().create(this.getProductsByKey(keys)[0]);
9680        }
9681        return product;
9682    }

9832     */
9833    public Exchange getExchangeForKey(int exchangeKey)
9834        throws SystemException, CommunicationException, AuthorizationException, NotFoundException
9835    {
9836        ExchangeStruct exchange = null;
9837        if (exchangeCache != null)
9838        {
9839            for (int i = 0; i < exchangeCache.length; ++i)
9840            {
9841                if (exchangeCache[i].exchangeKey == exchangeKey)
9842                {
9843                    exchange = exchangeCache[i];
9844                    break;
9845                }
9846            }
9847        }
9848        else
9849        {
9850            if (GUILoggerHome.find().isDebugOn())
9851            {
9852                GUILoggerHome.find().debug(TRANSLATOR_NAME + ":getExchangeForKey", GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.PRODUCT_DEFINITION, new Integer(exchangeKey));
9853            }
9854            exchange = exchangeService.getExchangeForKey(exchangeKey);
9855        }
9856        if (exchange == null)
9857        {
9858            throw new NotFoundException();
9859        }
9860        return ExchangeFactoryImpl.create(exchange);
9861    }

9946    /**
9947     * Subscribes the client listener to receive UserMaintenanceEventService
9948     * UserMaintenanceEventServiceAPI operation definition.
9949     *
9950     * @param clientListener the client listener to subscribe.
9951     * @throws SystemException
9952     * @throws CommunicationException
9953     * @throws AuthorizationException
9954     * @throws DataValidationException
9955     */
9956    public void subscribeUserMaintenanceEvent(EventChannelListener clientListener)
9957           throws SystemException, CommunicationException, AuthorizationException, DataValidationException
9958    {
9959        /* Server is not ready to publish user/firm delete or firm update as of Nov 10, 2001.
9960         */
9961 
9962        if (GUILoggerHome.find().isDebugOn())
9963        {
9964            GUILoggerHome.find().debug(TRANSLATOR_NAME + ":subscribeUserMaintenanceEventChannel", GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.USER_MANAGEMENT, clientListener);
9965        }
9966 
9967        ChannelKey myChannelKey = new ChannelKey(ChannelType.CB_USER_EVENT_ADD_USER, new Integer(0));
9968        int key1 = SubscriptionManagerFactory.find().subscribe(myChannelKey, clientListener, cacheUpdateConsumer);
9969        myChannelKey = new ChannelKey(ChannelType.CB_USER_EVENT_DELETE_USER, new Integer(0));
9970        int key2 = SubscriptionManagerFactory.find().subscribe(myChannelKey, clientListener, cacheUpdateConsumer);
9971 
9972        myChannelKey = new ChannelKey(ChannelType.CB_USER_EVENT_ADD_FIRM, new Integer(0));
9973        int key3 = SubscriptionManagerFactory.find().subscribe(myChannelKey, clientListener, cacheUpdateConsumer);
9974        myChannelKey = new ChannelKey(ChannelType.CB_USER_EVENT_DELETE_FIRM, new Integer(0));
9975        int key4 = SubscriptionManagerFactory.find().subscribe(myChannelKey, clientListener, cacheUpdateConsumer);
9976 
9977        myChannelKey = new ChannelKey(ChannelType.CB_USER_EVENT_USER_FIRM_AFFILIATION_UPDATE, new Integer(0));
9978        int key5 = SubscriptionManagerFactory.find().subscribe(myChannelKey, clientListener, cacheUpdateConsumer);
9979 
9980        myChannelKey = new ChannelKey(ChannelType.CB_USER_EVENT_USER_FIRM_AFFILIATION_DELETE, new Integer(0));
9981        int key6 = SubscriptionManagerFactory.find().subscribe(myChannelKey, clientListener, cacheUpdateConsumer);
9982 
9983        if (key1 == 1 && key2 == 1 && key3 == 1 && key4 == 1 && key5 == 1 && key6 == 1)
9984        {

9986            {

9990        }

10367    public void subscribeAlertEvent(EventChannelListener clientListener)
10368            throws DataValidationException, AuthorizationException, CommunicationException, SystemException
10369    {
10370        if (GUILoggerHome.find().isDebugOn() && GUILoggerHome.find().isPropertyOn(GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.ALERTS))
10371        {
10372            GUILoggerHome.find().debug(TRANSLATOR_NAME + ":subscribeAlertEvent", GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.ALERTS);
10373        }
10374 
10375        ChannelKey key = new ChannelKey(ChannelType.CB_ALERT, new Integer(0));
10376        int subscriptionCount1 = SubscriptionManagerFactory.find().subscribe(key, clientListener, alertConsumer);
10377        key = new ChannelKey(ChannelType.CB_ALERT_SATISFACTION, new Integer(0));
10378        int subscriptionCount2 = SubscriptionManagerFactory.find().subscribe(key, clientListener, alertConsumer);
10379        key = new ChannelKey(ChannelType.CB_ALERT_UPDATE, new Integer(0));
10380        int subscriptionCount3 = SubscriptionManagerFactory.find().subscribe(key, clientListener, alertConsumer);
10381        if (subscriptionCount1 == 1 && subscriptionCount2 == 1 && subscriptionCount3 == 1)
10382        {
10383            // subscribe the consumer to the CAS
10384            subscribeAlertEvent(alertConsumer);
10385        }
10386    }

10397        int subscriptionCount1 = SubscriptionManagerFactory.find().unsubscribe(key, clientListener, alertConsumer);
10398        key = new ChannelKey(ChannelType.CB_ALERT_SATISFACTION, new Integer(0));
10399        int subscriptionCount2 = SubscriptionManagerFactory.find().unsubscribe(key, clientListener, alertConsumer);
10400        key = new ChannelKey(ChannelType.CB_ALERT_UPDATE, new Integer(0));
10401        int subscriptionCount3 = SubscriptionManagerFactory.find().unsubscribe(key, clientListener, alertConsumer);

11318 
11319    /**
11320     * Methos used to convert the model object into structs and call the service.
11321     */
11322    public void createElementsForGroup(long groupKey, List<GroupElementModel> newGroupElements)
11323            throws SystemException, TransactionFailedException, CommunicationException, AuthorizationException, DataValidationException
11324    {
11325        ElementEntryStruct[] newElements = new ElementEntryStruct[newGroupElements.size()];
11326        int i = 0;
11327        for (GroupElementModel newGroupElement : newGroupElements)
11328        {
11329            newElements[i++] = newGroupElement.toElementEntryStruct();
11330        }
11331 
11332        IGUILogger guiLogger = GUILoggerHome.find();
11333        if (guiLogger.isDebugOn() &&
11334                guiLogger.isPropertyOn(GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.USER_MANAGEMENT))
11335        {
11336            guiLogger.debug(TRANSLATOR_NAME + "createElementsForGroup: groupKey:",
11337                                       GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.USER_MANAGEMENT, groupKey);
11338            guiLogger.debug(TRANSLATOR_NAME + "createElementsForGroup: elements:",
11339                                       GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.USER_MANAGEMENT, newElements);
11340        }
11341 
11342        ElementErrorResultStruct[] resultStructs = groupService.createElementsForGroup(groupKey, newElements);
11343 
11344        StringBuilder errorString = new StringBuilder(256);
11345        Set<GroupElementModel> alreadyExistElements = new HashSet<GroupElementModel>();
11346        for (int j = 0; j < resultStructs.length; j++)
11347        {
11348            ElementErrorResultStruct resultStruct = resultStructs[j];
11349            GroupElementModel elementModel = new GroupElementModelImpl(resultStruct.elementStruct);
11350            // if successful, convert returned struct to model object and add to cache
11351            if (resultStruct.errorCode != 1)
11352            {
11353                if (DataValidationCodes.GROUPELEMENT_ALREADY_EXISTS == resultStruct.errorCode)
11354                {
11355                    elementModel = groupElementCache.findElementKeyByUniqueSearchHashCode(elementModel);
11356                    if (elementModel != null)
11357                    {
11358                        alreadyExistElements.add(elementModel);
11359                    }
11360                    else
11361                    {
11362                        errorString.append(resultStruct.errorMessage).append("\n");
11363                    }
11364                }
11365                else
11366                {
11367                    errorString.append(resultStruct.errorMessage).append("\n");
11368                }
11369            }
11370        }
11371 
11372        // if there is any already existing element call addElementsToGroup
11373        if (alreadyExistElements.size() > 0)
11374        {
11375            try
11376            {
11377                addElementsToGroup(groupKey, alreadyExistElements);
11378            }
11379            catch (DataValidationException e)
11380            {
11381                errorString.append(e.getMessage()).append("\n");
11382            }
11383        }
11384 
11385        // if there is any error from the service, generate DataValidationException
11386        if (errorString.length() > 0)
11387        {
11388            throw ExceptionBuilder.dataValidationException(errorString.toString(), 0);
11389        }
11390    }
11391 
11392 
11393    /**
11394     * Methos used to convert the model object into structs and call the service.
11395     */
11396    public void addElementsToGroup(long groupKey, Set<GroupElementModel> groupElements)
11397            throws SystemException, TransactionFailedException, CommunicationException, AuthorizationException, DataValidationException
11398    {
11399 
11400        long[] elements = new long[groupElements.size()];
11401        int i = 0;
11402        for (GroupElementModel element : groupElements)
11403        {
11404            elements[i++] = element.getElementKey();
11405        }
11406 
11407        IGUILogger guiLogger = GUILoggerHome.find();
11408        if (guiLogger.isDebugOn() &&
11409                guiLogger.isPropertyOn(GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.USER_MANAGEMENT))
11410        {
11411            guiLogger.debug(TRANSLATOR_NAME + "addElementsToGroup: groupKey:",
11412                                       GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.USER_MANAGEMENT, groupKey);
11413            guiLogger.debug(TRANSLATOR_NAME + "addElementsToGroup: elements:",
11414                                       GUILoggerSABusinessProperty.USER_MANAGEMENT, elements);
11415        }
11416 
11417        ErrorStruct[] resultStructs = groupService.addElementsToGroup(groupKey, elements);
11418        StringBuilder errorString = new StringBuilder(256);
11419        List<GroupElementModel> notFoundElements = new ArrayList<GroupElementModel>();
11420        for (int j = 0; j < resultStructs.length; j++)
11421        {
11422            // if successful, add to cache
11423            GroupElementModel elementModel = groupElementCache.getGroupElementByElementKey(elements[j]);
11424            ErrorStruct resultStruct = resultStructs[j];
11425            if (resultStruct.errorCode != 1)
11426            {
11427                if (DataValidationCodes.INVALID_GROUPELEMENT == resultStruct.errorCode &&
11428                        groupElementCache.findElementKeyByUniqueSearchHashCode(elementModel) == null)
11429                {
11430                    notFoundElements.add(elementModel);
11431                }
11432                else
11433                {
11434                    errorString.append(resultStruct.errorMessage).append("\n");
11435                }
11436            }
11437        }
11438 
11439        // check if notFound elements are present than call createElementsForGroup
11440        if (notFoundElements.size() > 0)
11441        {
11442            try
11443            {
11444                createElementsForGroup(groupKey, notFoundElements);
11445            }

11595

11597 
11598        SubscriptionManagerImpl subscriptionManager = SubscriptionManagerFactory.find();
11599        ChannelKey myChannelKey = new ChannelKey(ChannelType.GROUP_ADD_ELEMENT, new Integer(0));
11600        int key1 = subscriptionManager.subscribe(myChannelKey, clientListener, groupElementConsumer);
11601 
11602        myChannelKey = new ChannelKey(ChannelType.GROUP_UPDATE_ELEMENT, new Integer(0));

11609        {
11610            groupElementEvent.subscribeGroupElementEvent(groupElementConsumer);
11611        }
11612    }

12383    public String getWorkStationID()
12384    {
12385        String workStationInfo;
12386        try
12387        {
12388            InetAddress addr = InetAddress.getLocalHost();
12389            workStationInfo = addr.getHostAddress();
12390        }
12391        catch (UnknownHostException uhe)
12392        {
12393            workStationInfo = getCurrentLoggedInUser();
12394            GUILoggerHome.find().exception("Work station IP not found -- will user UserID '" + workStationInfo
12395                    + "' as unique identifier", uhe);
12396        }
12397        return workStationInfo;
12398    }

12410    public String createTimeStamp()
12411    {
12412        StringBuilder timeStamp = new StringBuilder();
12413        Calendar cal = new GregorianCalendar();
12414        timeStamp.append(cal.get(Calendar.DATE)).append(':')
12415                .append(cal.get(Calendar.MONTH)).append(':')
12416                .append(cal.get(Calendar.YEAR)).append(':')
12417 
12418                .append(cal.get(Calendar.HOUR)).append(':')
12419                .append(cal.get(Calendar.MINUTE)).append(':')
12420                .append(cal.get(Calendar.SECOND));
12421        return timeStamp.toString();
12422    }
